sentences: Elena Barbara Giuranna (18 November 1899 – 31 July 1998) was an Italian pianist and composer.
After completing her studies, Giuranna taught at the Rome Conservatory from 1937 to 1970 and worked as an editor of 18th-century music.
She was a music consultant to RAI in Rome from 1948 to 1956, and she was elected a member of the Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia in 1982.
